      "description": "<b>Gandalf</b><sprite name=\"commander\">[1]<sprite name=\"agent\">[1]<sprite name=\"emmissary\">[1]<sprite name=\"mage\"><mark=#00ff00>[3]</mark><br><br><b>Starting Population Centers:</b><br>- Hobbiton <sprite name=\"pc\"/>[2]<sprite name=\"fort\"/><mark=#ff0000>[0]</mark><br><br><b>Starting Characters:</b><br>- Frodo <sprite name=\"commander\"/>[1]<br>- Sam <sprite name=\"agent\"/>[1]<br>- Pippin <sprite name=\"emmissary\"/>[1]<br>- Merry <sprite name=\"agent\"/>[1]<br><br><b>Starting Armies:</b><br>- <mark=#ff0000>No</mark> armies<br><br><b>Starting Magic:</b><br>- <mark=#00ff00>Many</mark> spells <sprite name=\"spell\"/> and artifacts <sprite name=\"artifact\"/><br><br><b>Difficulty</b>: <mark=#ff0000>Hard</mark><br><b>Starting power</b>: <mark=#ff0000>Small</mark><br><b>Recruitable allies</b>: <mark=#00ff00>Plenty</mark><br><b>Recruitable armies</b>: <mark=#ff0000>Scarce</mark><br><br><b>Gameplay style</b>:<br>- Characters and artifacts search",
      "joinedTitle": "The unexpected fate of the Ring",
      "joinedText": "Frodo… there’s something I never told you.<br><br>I always said I kept the ring with me. Every breath.<br><br>But there was one night when I took it off—just for a heartbeat. I needed silence. I meant to pick it up again immediately.<br><br>But something happened.<br><br>I must have closed my eyes. Then suddenly it was morning, and the ring was gone.<br>No sound. No trail. Just absence.<br><br>I searched. Days, maybe weeks. Time felt wrong. The harder I looked, the more it felt like the ring wasn’t lost — it had moved on.<br><br>And I’m sorry, Frodo… truly. I never meant for the burden to fall on you. But it has.<br><br>Gandalf will guide you now, my boy… where I could not.",
